spans.text: would she oft delighted rove The slower-enamelled vale along
Her heart a stranger to disguise , Her mind
the tender strain , She heard my sighs
no more than truth , And all my love was well repaid
OH who , that heard her vows erewhile ,
that saw her smile , That fraud could find admittance there
) OH cheer my spirit with a sigh , And grave these lines upon my tomb
